article.headline: Oral Roberts 75, UMKC 68
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Ken Tutt scored 21 points to lead Oral Roberts to a 75-68 victory over Missouri-Kansas City Saturday. The Golden Eagles (11-7, 4-0 Mid-Continent) never trailed in the game after scoring the first nine points in the game, but the Kangaroos (7-12, 2-1) made it close down the stretch. UMKC, which trailed 48-30 with 15:30 left in the game, cut the margin to three on a steal and dunk by Dane Brumagin with 1:39 remaining in the contest. The Kangaroos could get no closer as the Golden Eagles connected on eight-of-10 free throws in the last 50 seconds to seal their fifth consecutive victory. Freshman Dominique Johnson, who led UMKC with 18 points, fueled the comeback with 13 points in the last 6:19. It was the inside strength of Oral Roberts that proved to be the difference. The Golden Eagles outrebounded UMKC 46-32 led by Caleb Green and Shawn King with 10 each. The Kangaroos stayed close enough to forge a comeback because of poor free throw shooting by Oral Roberts. The Golden Eagles were just 26-of-41 from the line for 63 percent. Tutt was six-of-11 from the floor, including four-of-nine from behind the three-point line. He hit three-of-four free throws in the last 38 seconds. Green followed Tutt with 19 points and King added 10. Johnson came off the bench to lead UMKC. He was seven-of-12 from the floor and three-of-six behind the three-point line. Brumagin added 16 and Quinton Day had 14. Day moved into fifth place on the UMKC career-scoring list. He has 1,214 points to go past David Robinson who had 1,211. Brumagin was the top rebounder for the Kangaroos with five.
